# Frontend CSP (StrictPolicyPreset)

Before adding or changing frontend behavior, read `app/Support/Csp/StrictPolicyPreset.php`. It is the source of truth for the enforced CSP header.

## Policy summary

- **No `unsafe-inline` or `unsafe-eval`** for scripts/styles. Inline `<script>` and `<style>` must use a nonce (`Vite::cspNonce()` in Blade; pass nonce to `@fluxAppearance` / `@fluxScripts`).
- **Scripts** load only from app origins plus `'wasm-unsafe-eval'` (WebAssembly). Turnstile adds `https://challenges.cloudflare.com` when `turnstile.enabled` is true.
- **Styles** load only from app origins (nonce required for inline).
- **Connect (fetch/XHR/WebSocket)** must target allowed origins: app origins, `https://api.pwnedpasswords.com`, Turnstile (if enabled), and Vite HMR WebSocket origins in local/testing only.
- **Frames** are `'none'` unless Turnstile is enabled (`frame-src https://challenges.cloudflare.com`).
- **Workers** allow app origins plus `blob:`.
- **`object-src`** and **`frame-ancestors`** are `'none'`.

## Frontend do / don't

- **Do** bundle JS through Vite (`@vite`) instead of CDN `<script>` tags.
- **Do** use Tailwind/Flux classes instead of inline `style="..."` or Alpine `x-bind:style`.
- **Do** avoid Alpine template literals in `x-text`, `x-show`, and `x-bind:*` (backticks break CSP). Use string concatenation or bound properties instead.
- **Do** add new external origins to `StrictPolicyPreset` (and `tests/Feature/ContentSecurityPolicyTest.php`), not only the frontend file.
- **Don't** add third-party scripts, styles, images, fonts, iframes, or `fetch`/WebSocket targets without updating the preset.
- **Don't** rely on `eval()`, `new Function()`, or dynamic inline script injection.

## Local Vite dev

In `local`/`testing`, the preset allows Vite HMR origins (`:5173`, `vite.{host}`, loopback only when the app URL is loopback). If assets fail to load in dev, check CSP before blaming Vite.

## Verification

After CSP-related frontend changes, run:

```bash
php artisan test --compact tests/Feature/ContentSecurityPolicyTest.php
```
